# .claudeignore
# These paths contain user-generated data and credentials.
# Claude Code must not read, modify, delete, or overwrite these files.

# NOTE — user data location changed in Phase 1 (Data Separation).
# User data now lives in a dynamic per-user folder: %USERPROFILE%\DawahDeskData\
# (e.g. C:\Users\hatem\DawahDeskData\)
# This path cannot be listed here because it varies by machine and user account.
# The entries below cover only the legacy server/data/ location, which will contain
# .migrated marker files after first run. Do not delete those files.
server/data/runtime-state.json
server/data/runtime-state.json.migrated
server/data/ops/
server/data/ops.migrated/
server/data/backups/
server/data/backups.migrated/
secrets/
